cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.PL 

This paper deals with formal logic and reasoning, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of ceteris paribus clauses and counterfactual reasoning suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The application of the framework to game forms and decision-making suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the use of alternative interpretations of ceteris paribus suggests it could belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
